Critical curriculum initialization bug.

Training starts immediately in WAYPOINT mode instead of foundational stabilize training.

This is completely wrong.

============================================================
REQUIRED BEHAVIOR
============================================================

When:

curriculum_enabled=true

AND:

curriculum_phase=stabilize

The simulator MUST start in:
STABILIZE mode ONLY.

============================================================
CURRENT BUG
============================================================

Some autonomous initialization logic is overriding the curriculum phase and activating:
WAYPOINT mode.

This must never happen.

============================================================
FIX REQUIRED
============================================================

Curriculum phase must fully override:
- mission manager
- autonomous mode scheduler
- default mode selection
- mission startup logic
- waypoint activation
- navigation initialization

============================================================
IMPLEMENT HARD OVERRIDE
============================================================

During env reset():

if curriculum_enabled:

    active_mode = curriculum_mode

    disable mission-driven transitions
    disable autonomous startup selection
    disable waypoint activation

============================================================
EXPECTED BEHAVIOR
============================================================

If:
curriculum_phase=stabilize

Then after reset:
active_mode MUST ALWAYS equal STABILIZE.

No exceptions.

============================================================
IMPORTANT
============================================================

During isolated curriculum phases:
- mission manager should be bypassed
- waypoint logic disabled
- navigation targets ignored

The aircraft should ONLY learn the requested skill.

============================================================
ONLY ENABLE MISSION SYSTEM WHEN:
============================================================

curriculum_phase == mixed

OR:
curriculum_enabled == false

============================================================
ADD DEBUG OUTPUT
============================================================

On every env reset print:

CURRICULUM ENABLED
CURRICULUM PHASE = STABILIZE
ACTIVE MODE = STABILIZE
MISSION MANAGER ENABLED = FALSE

============================================================
ADD ASSERTIONS
============================================================

if curriculum_phase == "stabilize":
    assert active_mode == STABILIZE

if curriculum_phase != "mixed":
    assert mission_manager_enabled == False

============================================================
VISUALIZATION
============================================================

Display prominently:
CURRENT CURRICULUM PHASE
CURRENT ACTIVE MODE

During stabilize training:
both MUST remain STABILIZE.

============================================================
FINAL REQUIREMENT
============================================================

The trainer must NEVER start directly in WAYPOINT mode during stabilize curriculum.

Foundational stabilization training MUST happen first before any navigation tasks are introduced.